The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, April 22, 2004 				 Jaya summons
																								Tiruchirappalli, April 21 (PTI): A local court has summoned Jayalalithaa on a petition by Congress and DMK activists charging her for describing Congress chief Sonia Gandhi as a foreigner at election meets. 																								The petition said Sonia had been granted Indian citizenship in 1983. Hence, the chief ministers description of Sonia as a foreigner was not only a violation, but a disobedience of the court order. 
